title.@value: Spinal or epidural anaesthesia-induced headache during pregnancy

definition.@value: A condition affecting females during pregnancy, caused by the administration of spinal and epidural anaesthesia. This condition is characterised by cephalgia during pregnancy.

label.@value: Spinal or epidural anaesthesia-induced headache during pregnancy
spinal and epidural anaesthesia induced headache during pregnancy, unspecified trimester
